curseForgeProject.summary: [Forge/Fabric] Adds 35+ new animals to your world, with items, food, blocks, and armor.

screenshots.description: Cowardly herbivores found in all sorts of forests. They run from larger mobs, but can be bred with wheat or carrots
screenshots.title: Deer

screenshots.description: Sharks are predatory fish found in the oceans. They may attack players who have already been damaged, as they smell the fresh blood, but do not attack healthy players. Other mobs are not as fortunate...
screenshots.title: Sharks

screenshots.description: Voracious fish found in jungle ponds. They only attack when their target is weak. Rumour has it they can strip a person or horse clean to  the bones...
screenshots.title: Piranha

screenshots.description: Coyotes are opportunistic hunters and scavengers, and will even attempt to prey on players in the night. However, in the day they can be tamed with raw rabbit or chicken. They spawn in deserts, mesas, and plains.
screenshots.title: Coyotes

screenshots.description: Large birds found in deserts and mountains. They eat bone marrow, and will grab skeletons and drop them down to break their bones open. They can be tamed with bones
screenshots.title: Lammergeier/Bearded Vulture

screenshots.description: Comes in both saltwater and freshwater variants, they're neutral, but don't hold food near them...
screenshots.title: Eels

screenshots.description: Even bigger than their cohorts, and are much nastier. Some believe they can rip you from your boat in the night and crack your skull with their beak
screenshots.title: Giant Squid

screenshots.description: Badgers can be found in forests, savannas, and taigas, and will prey on smaller animals such as chickens. If attacked, badgers will throw dirt and other such materials at the attacker, on top of using their sharp claws
screenshots.title: Badgers

screenshots.description: Whimsical fish found in warmer oceans, they may jump from the water and glide a bit
screenshots.title: Flying Fish

screenshots.description: Hostile wolves found in forests and taigas. If a player wears the head of a Dragon, they can tame these beasts with bones. Killing a feral wolf may drop their head, as well as some pelts, which can be made into capes, leather, and wool
screenshots.title: (Updated) Feral Wolves

screenshots.description: These harmless living fossils can be found in beaches and oceans, and drop bonemeal and their meat when killed
screenshots.title: Horseshoe Crab

screenshots.description: Moose are large members of the deer family found in taigas and swamps. Moose are a force to be reckoned with, but slaying one nets you a lot of venison and possibly a head.
screenshots.title: Moose

screenshots.description: Reindeer can be found in any cold biome, and can be bred with wheat or carrots. Reindeer can also be ridden!
screenshots.title: Reindeer

screenshots.description: Jellyfish spawn in water and float aimlessly, but don't touch them! They will inflict poison and blindness!
screenshots.title: Jellyfish

screenshots.description: Despite their textures, any 2 adults can breed with pumpkin seeds, and drop their meat when killed. Pheasants also peak at the ground!
screenshots.title: A Flock of Pheasants in a forest

screenshots.description: Neutral semi-aquatic animals, drop leather and blubber when killed, but won't give up easily.  But who was the walrus?
screenshots.title: Walrus

screenshots.description: Neutral and befriendable cephalopods found in oceans. Give them fish and they will be quite powerful allies. That is, as long as you avoid the blue-rings
screenshots.title: Octopus

screenshots.description: Turkeys are semi-neutral, semi-timid birds found in forests and similar. They will attack back, but scatter afterwards. When attacking or breeding, they flare their tail. Killing one may give you a nice feast! Any 2 adults can breed with pumpkin seeds.
screenshots.title: Turkeys

screenshots.description: Lampreys are parasitic fish. They will cling onto things bigger than them in order to suck their blood. Be careful in water!
screenshots.title: Lampreys

screenshots.description: Whales are (mostly) peaceful mammals found swimming in the oceans of Minecraftia. That doesn't mean its a good idea to annoy them.
screenshots.title: Whales

screenshots.description: Large, predatory squids found in deep oceans at night... don't get too close
screenshots.title: Colossal Squid

screenshots.description: Boars are vicious piggies found in many biomes, including forests, jungles, and savannas. Some will attack larger creatures on sight, and most will attack smaller creatures like chickens and pheasants. Drop pork meat and sometimes their head.
screenshots.title: Boar

screenshots.description: Crabs can be found on Beaches and in Swamps, and drop Crab Meat and Bonemeal when killed. Crabs also like to party, but they won't join any ol party
screenshots.title: Crabs

screenshots.description: Found in oceans, Bobbit Worms bury their entire body aside from their vicious mouths into soft sediment in order to ambush passing prey, including people.
screenshots.title: Bobbit Worm

screenshots.description: Aggressive predatory fish found in open waters in warmer climates. They are strong enough to break bones by ramming targets! Known for their attraction to shiny armor.
screenshots.title: Barracuda
